  "response": "The Hindi word \"\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935\" (Bhedbhaav) translates to **discrimination** in English. It refers to:\n\n*   **Differentiation:** Distinguishing between people or things.\n*   **Partiality:** Favoring one person or group over another.\n*   **Bias:** Prejudice or unfairness against a person or group.\n*   **Discrimination:** Unjust or prejudicial treatment of different categories of people or things, especially on the grounds of race, age, sex, or disability.\n\nEssentially, it encompasses any unfair treatment or distinction based on prejudice or unjustifiable factors.",
